This folder contains my learning summary from a beginner-level Linux course. I used these commands and concepts while practicing in Kali Linux and preparing for a career as a security analyst.

✅ Topics I Learned
🔹 Linux Command Line Basics
ls, cd, pwd, mkdir, rm, touch, clear

Navigating the file system using relative and absolute paths

🔹 File Permissions & Management
chmod, chown, ls -l, and permission types: read, write, execute

Understanding users, groups, and file access control

🔹 Process Management
Using ps, top, and kill to view and manage running processes

🔹 Package Management
Installing and updating software with apt, apt-get, and dpkg

🔹 Networking Commands
Basics of ping, ifconfig, netstat, traceroute

🔹 Searching and Filtering
grep, find, cat, head, tail, less, more

🔐 Why It Matters in Cybersecurity
Linux is widely used in cybersecurity, especially in tools like Kali Linux. 
Learning these commands has helped me understand how systems work, how to investigate logs, and how attackers and defenders operate in Linux-based environments.
